==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|salarium||lang=la|salt money, money to buy salt with}}, from {{term|sal||lang=la|salt}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-salary.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{homophones|celery}} (in some dialects)

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=salaries}}

# a fixed amount of [[money]] paid to a worker, usually measured on a monthly or annual basis, not hourly, as [[wages]]. Implies a degree of professionalism and/or autonomy.

